# CalDAV connection. Copy to `.env` (gitignored) if you need to override defaults.
# Values are Metro-inlined into the JS bundle at BUILD time — restart/rebuild after edits.
#
# Credentials are SERVER-SIDE by design (Caddy injects Authorization on /dav/* —
# see docs/Deploy.md). Clients normally need a URL only:
#
#   web:      no .env needed at all — defaults to `/dav/` on the page's own origin
#             (dev proxy on :8880 and the deployed site both work zero-config)
#   Android:  REQUIRED at APK build time — the deployed injected endpoint, e.g.
#             https://<host>:<mitsume-port>/dav/   (never commit the real URL)
EXPO_PUBLIC_DAV_URL=

# OPTIONAL dev fallback only: when set, the client attaches Basic auth itself —
# useful for Android dev pointing straight at Radicale without the proxy.
# Leave unset in every normal flow; never needed for web.
#EXPO_PUBLIC_DAV_USER=
#EXPO_PUBLIC_DAV_PASS=
